Does it matter if the closest is in the past or future?  In other words, are you looking for the closest next datetime or the absolute closest datetime?

```yaml
# The following assume you have a variable, dt_list, that holds 
# a list of datetime objects 

#Next closest
{%- set now_var = now() %}
{%- set new_list = ([now_var] + dt_list)|sort %}
{%- set now_index = new_list.index(now_var) %}
{{ new_list[now_index+1]}}

#Past closest
{%- set now_var = now() %}
{%- set new_list = ([now_var] + dt_list)|sort %}
{%- set now_index = new_list.index(now_var) %}
{{ new_list[now_index-1]}}
 
#Absolute closest
{%- set now_var = now() %}
{%- set new_list = ([now_var] + dt_list)|sort %}
{%- set now_index = new_list.index(now_var) %}
{% if now_index == 0 %}
  {{ new_list[1] }}
{% elif now_index == new_list|count-1 %}
  {{ new_list[-2] }}
{% else %}
  {%- set remaining = new_list[now_index-1:now_index+2] %}
  {{remaining[0] if (remaining[0] - now_var > now_var - remaining[2]) else remaining[2] }} 
{% endif %}
```
